<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5209> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5209" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate, honored at Lissus (CIL 12.2.759). Probably a Legate under Caesar soon after his tribunate of the Plebs in 57." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5089> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5089" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "With Serranus, he opposed the moves for Cicero's recall (Cic. Sest. 72, 82, and 94; Pis. 35; Mil. 39; Ascon. 11 C; Schol. Bob. 122, and 134 Stangl)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4970> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4970" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor in Africa (CIL 12.2.2513-ILS 9482). The date is only approximate: he became Tribune of the Plebs in 57." .
